# Admin Cross-Client Consistency

## Rule: Admin changes must be applied to all clients

When making any change to admin infrastructure, features, or fixes — whether in `packages/admin-core` or in an app-level admin route — that change must be reflected across **every** client app and `apps/client-template`.

### Client apps that must stay in sync:
- `apps/northbound-treatment`
- `apps/inner-peak-colorado`
- `apps/cipher-billing`
- `apps/sweet-media`
- `apps/addiction-interventions`
- `apps/rize-oc`
- `apps/simple-health`
- `apps/mountainview-treatment`
- `apps/client-template` (canonical scaffold — always update this first)

### What counts as an admin change that requires cross-client rollout:

| Change type | Example |
|---|---|
| New API route under `/api/admin/` | `/api/admin/revalidate`, `/api/admin/generate-seo-meta` |
| New env var required by admin features | `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` |
| Admin layout or auth changes | `AdminGuard` path matching fix |
| New `tracked_pages` / `blog_posts` DB column | requires migration SQL for each brand |
| New Supabase schema or RLS policy | update `client-template-schema.sql` + call out per-brand migration SQL |

### Workflow

1. Implement the change in `apps/client-template` and `packages/admin-core` first.
2. Then port any app-level files (API routes, env vars) to each client app.
3. For DB/schema changes: update `apps/client-template/supabase/client-template-schema.sql` and explicitly provide migration SQL for each existing brand.
4. When deploying env vars (e.g. `OPENROUTER_API_KEY`), add to all Vercel projects — not just the one being worked on.

### Never
- Never implement an admin feature in only one client app without porting it to the others.
- Never assume a Supabase schema change on one brand's project is live on another — each brand has its own isolated Supabase project.
